<TITLE> BSF abducts farmer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com) Indian Border Security Force on Friday abducted a Bangladeshi farmer from Shingnagar border of Chapainawabganj, BDR officials said. The abducted farmer was identified as Shakib Mia, 45, son of Zamidar Mia of Monakasha union at Shibganj upazila. Major Nazrul Islam, operation officer of Chapainawabganj 39 Rifles Battalion, said Maldaha 151 BSF Battalion soldiers of Daulatpur camp in India crossed the border and entered about 100 meters into Bangladesh at around 9.30am. They took Sakib along with them while he had been working in the field. Islam said they had sent a letter to BSF asking them to return the farmer. A flag meeting between BDR and BSF was also scheduled along the Shingnagar border for 3pm. bdn
